Brown meat in oil in nonstick skillet on medium-high heat. Remove from skillet; set aside. Add garlic, tomatoes, broth and basil to skillet; bring to boil. Stir in rice; return to boil. Reduce heat to medium-low. Stir in meat and Velveeta; cover. Simmer 8 to 10 min. or until heated through. Stir until Velveeta is completely melted and mixture is well blended.